1. Add in your gitlab ci\cd variables:

 - CI_REGISTRY - must contain docker.io.
 - CI_REGISTRY_IMAGE - must contain index.docker.io/username/image_name.
 - CI_REGISTRY_PASSWORD - must contain your Docker HUB password or your access token.
 - CI_REGISTRY_USER - must contain your Docker HUB username.

2. Create folder ~/www/devops and add add deploy binary+deploy.sh there.

3. Start "deploy" binary (deploy app works on 5000 port) and your app's dockerfile.

4. Add webhooks on your gitlab with "adress_your_server:5000".

5. Go to address on your server "127.0.0.1:5000" and you start process of deploy, it will listen this
address and start deploy.sh.
